ntry_ids":["n27274","n27275"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%B7%D9%8E%D9%88%D9%8E%D9%91%D8%B1%D9%8E"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of طَارَ (ṭāra) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb","uncountable"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"time, stage, phase, stadium","examples":[{"text":"وَأَشَارَ إِلَى أَنَّهُ “مُذْ أَقْفَلَ ٱلْمَعْبَرَ وَأُقْفِلَتْ مَعَهُ ٱلْمَعَابِرُ ٱلشَّرْقِيَّةُ لِسُورِيَا ٱلْمُوصِلَةُ إِلَى ٱلدَّاخِلِ ٱلْعَرَبِيِّ، أُعْطِبَتْ ذَهَابًا وَإِيَابًا حَرَكَةُ ٱلتَّبَادُلِ ٱلتِّجَارِيِّ ٱلَّتِي سَنَكُونُ ٱلْآنَ فِي طَوْرِ إِعَادَةِ إِحْيَائِهَا مِنَ ٱلْأَرَاضِي ٱللُّبْنَانِيَّةِ إِلَى ٱلدَّاخِلِ ٱلسُّورِيِّ، وَمِنْهُ إِلَى ٱلدَّاخِلِ ٱلْأُرْدُنِيِّ مِنْ خِلَالِ ٱلْمَعْبَرِ ٱلْمُسْتَعَادِ إِلَى ٱلدَّوْلَةِ ٱلسُّورِيَّةِ، لِلْاِنْتِقَالِ إِلَى ٱلْعِرَاقِ وَدُوَلِ ٱلْخَلِيجِ (ٱلْفَارِسِيِّ)”."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"mode","examples":[{"text":"طَوْر الْقِصَّة","english":"campaign/story mode"}]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to further, to bring forward, to develop"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"mountain","tags":["Classical"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Borrowed from Aramaic טוּרָא / ܛܘܪܐ (ṭūrā, “mountain, high territory”). Ultimately from Proto-West Semitic *ṯ̣ūr-. Doublet of ظِرّ (ẓirr) and زُرَر (zurar, “flint”)."},"ipa":["/tˤawr/","/tˤaw.wa.ra/","/tˤuːr/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n27274","headword_ar":"طَوْرٌ","root":"Twr","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A time; one time; like the French"},{"kind":"text","text":"“ fois; ” syn."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taArapN","text_ar":"تَارَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S, A, O, Msb, K:) pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aTowaArN","text_ar":"اَطْوَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, K, A.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^atayotuhu TaworFA baEoda TaworK","text_ar":"اَتَيْتُهُ طَوْرًا بَعْدَ طَوْرٍ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I came to him time after time."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"faEala *`lika TaworFA baEoda TaworK","text_ar":"فَعَلَ ذٰلِكَ طَوْرًا بَعْدَ طَوْرٍ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He did that time after time."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jiy^otuhu","text_ar":"جِيْتُهُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aTowaArFA","text_ar":"اَطْوَارًا"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I came to him several times."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A.) ―         -b2-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"State; condition; quality, mode,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"manner;"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"form,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"appearance:"},{"kind":"text","text":"pl."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aTowaArN","text_ar":"اَطْوَارٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Msb.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aln~aAsu A^aTowaArN","text_ar":"النَّاسُ اَطْوَارٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Mankind are of divers sorts and conditions."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A. *) It is said in the Kur [lxxi. 13],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"waqado xalaqakumo A^aTowaArFA","text_ar":"وَقَدْ خَلَقَكُمْ اَطْوَارًا"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"And He hath created you of divers sorts and conditions:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of different forms, every one of his proper form:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Th, TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of various aspects and dispositions:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"one time, a clot of blood; and one time, a lump of flesh:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Akh, S:) or ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"one time,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"seed; then, a clot of blood; then, a lump of flesh; then, bone."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Fr, TA.) ―         -b3-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Quantity; measure; extent:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"limit:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a limit between two things."},{"kind":"text","text":"(O, K.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EadaA fulaAnN Taworahu","text_ar":"عَدَا فُلَانٌ طَوْرَهُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one exceeded his proper measure,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"extent:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"his proper limit:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, O, TA:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taEad~aY","text_ar":"تَعَدَّى"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Taworahu","text_ar":"طَوْرَهُ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he transgressed the limits of his proper state,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"condition."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, TA.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A thing that is commensurate,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L, K, TA,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"equal in length"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"and breadth"},{"kind":"text","text":"(see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EadaA='N","text_ar":"عَدَا=ءٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":")], (TA,) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"correspondent, to a thing;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(L, K, TA;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TuwrN","text_ar":"طُورٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TawaArN","text_ar":"طَوَارٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K.) You say of anything that is the equal of another thing, ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa Tuwruhu","text_ar":"هُوَ طُورُهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TawaAruhu","text_ar":"طَوَارُهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It is the equal of it."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Aboo-Bekr, TA.) You say also,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h`*aA AlHaAy^iTi","text_ar":"هٰذَا الحَايِطِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"raA^ayotu HabolFA biTawaAri","text_ar":"رَاَيْتُ حَبْلًا بِطَوَارِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I saw a rope of the length of this wall."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h`*ihi Ald~aAru","text_ar":"هٰذِهِ الدَّارُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"h`*ihi Ald~aAri","text_ar":"هٰذِهِ الدَّارِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biTawaAri","text_ar":"بِطَوَارِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"This house has its wall contiguous to the wall of this"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"other"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"house, in one rank,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"series."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"daArK","text_ar":"دَارٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TawaAru","text_ar":"طَوَارُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, O, K,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"dAr","text_ar":"دار"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TiwaAru","text_ar":"طِوَارُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaworuhaA","text_ar":"طَوْرُهَا"},{"kind":"text","text":", and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TuwaratuhaA","text_ar":"طُوَرَتُهَا","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (O,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The part of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"finaA='","text_ar":"فِنَا=ء"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"exterior court,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"yard"},{"kind":"text","text":"],"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of a house, that is coextensive with the house;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, A, O, K; *)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jawaAruhu","text_ar":"جَوَارُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K in art."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jwr","text_ar":"جور"},{"kind":"text","text":".) [See also the next paragraph.]"}],"source_refs":["S","A","O","Msb","K","TA","Th","Akh","L"]},{"entry_id":"n27275","headword_ar":"طُورٌ","root":"Twr","body":[{"kind":"text","text":": see"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaworN","text_ar":"طَوْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", latter part, in two places. ―         -b2-  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"yard"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"finaA='","text_ar":"فِنَا=ء"},{"kind":"text","text":")"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of house;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TuwarapN","text_ar":"طُوَرَةٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) [See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TawaAr","text_ar":"طَوَار"},{"kind":"text","text":", voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"TaworN","text_ar":"طَوْرٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", last signification.]       -A2-"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A mountain:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, O, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"any mountain that produces trees,"},{"kind":"text","text":"otherwise a mountain is not so called. (R, TA.) [Hence"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlT~uwru","text_ar":"الطُّورُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is applied to Mount Sinai, which is also called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tuwru siynaA='a","text_ar":"طُورُ سِينَا=ءَ"},{"kind":"text","text":", and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Tuwru siyniyna","text_ar":"طُورُ سِينِينَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and to the Mount of Olives, and to several other mountains; as is said in the K &c.]"}],"source_refs":["S","O","K"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}